external_knowledge:
- "Top 3 most recent reviews" refers to the reviews ranked by the `created_at` timestamp in descending order, limited to the top 3 per source;
- "Overall score" is calculated as the sum of the `helpful_num` and `upvotes` minus the `downvotes` for each review;
- "Sources" are the origins of the reviews, such as app stores or web forms;
- "Resolved reviews" are those where the issue described in the review has been addressed, indicated by the `is_resolved` flag being set to 1.

- "most recent" refers to the review with the latest `created_at` timestamp;
- "top-rated" refers to the reviews with the highest `star_num` for each user;
- "above the average" means the `star_num` is greater than the average star rating of all reviews.

- "digital garden of user reviews" refers to the database containing user reviews for app versions;
- "English-speaking gardeners" refers to users whose preferred language is English;
- "most glowing stars" refers to star ratings greater than 3;
- "newest flowers that bloomed after the dawn of 2022" refers to app versions released after January 1, 2022;
- "top 5 praises" refers to the top 5 reviews ranked by star rating within each app version.

- 'Open' refers to the status of the review, meaning it is still under consideration or active;
- 'Russian' refers to the language of the review;
- 'Upvoted' means the review has received at least one positive vote from other users.

- "most recent app version" refers to the latest version of the app associated with a review;
- "user details" include the user's name and the content of their review;
- "feedback insights" encompass the type of feedback and the count of feedback entries;
- "organized by the version of the app, the name of the gardener, and the content of their notes" means the results are ordered by `version_number`, `user_name`, and `content`.

- 'Garden of app versions' refers to the set of app versions in the database;
- 'Blossomed after the dawn of 2020' means versions released after January 1, 2020;
- 'Tokens of appreciation' refers to user reviews;
- 'Star rating higher than a mere three' means reviews with a star rating greater than 3;
- 'Showered with more than five unique tokens' means there are more than 5 distinct reviews.

- A "resolver" refers to a user who changes the status of a review to resolved (status_id = 1);
- "Success rate" is the ratio of resolved reviews to the total number of reviews handled by a user;
- "Most efficient" means the user has a higher resolution rate than the average resolution rate across all users.

- 'Blossomed with at least one "Helpful" feedback' means the review has received at least one feedback type named 'Helpful';
- 'Prolific authors who have penned more than one review' refers to users who have written more than one review;
- 'Multilingual' indicates that the review is associated with more than one language;
- 'Marked as resolved' means the issue in the review has been resolved;
- 'Originating from the app store' means the review was submitted through the app store.

- "Most frequently occurring" refers to the review status with the highest count of reviews;
- "Beacon in a sea of reviews" is a metaphor for the most common review status, indicating it stands out among all other statuses;
- "Guiding the path for user feedback" suggests that understanding this status helps in managing and improving user interactions and feedback.

- "tongues" refers to languages;
- "subjects of more than 10 reviews" means that the language has been associated with more than 10 reviews;
- "rank in terms of the average star ratings" means the languages are ordered by the average star ratings given by users.

- "Recent" refers to within the last three months;
- "Resolved" refers to reviews where the issue has been addressed and `resolution_date` is not null;
- "Unresolved" refers to reviews where the issue has not been addressed and `resolution_date` is null;
- "Average star rating" is the mean of the star ratings given by users.

- 'Top 3 reviews' refers to the highest-ranked reviews based on the star rating within each app version;
- 'Blossomed with more than 3 stars' means the review has a star rating greater than 3;
- 'Deemed helpful by more than 5 users' means the review has been marked as helpful by more than 5 users.

- "resolved issues" refers to reviews where `is_resolved = 1` and `resolution_date IS NOT NULL`;
- "blossomed into a garden of diverse feedback types" refers to having more than one distinct `feedback_type_id`;
- "since the dawn of May 3, 2023" refers to `resolution_date > '2023-05-02'`.
